notesStmt.note: Inscription: "Wm. W. Turner, Esq.-- from his Friend Ch[...] Wexford -- NYork 1853 -- and to his Friend -- Alexander I. Coltheal -- from W.W. Turner" (flyleaf verso at back of book).

msContents.summary: Persian-learner's copy of the story. In some sections, the story appears on rectos, and glosser terms in Persian and English appear on the facing verso (f. 1v-9v); in other sections, the story appears on both recto and verso, with vocabulary items annotated in English in the margin (f. 46-113).

supportDesc.extent: ii, 111, i leaves : 224 x 182 (185 x 137) mm, bound to 227 x 184 x 21 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in large nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Red leather over pulpboard with faint gold-tooled (now greenish) frame of parallel lines; plain paper doublure.

origin.p: The item is undated, but an owner's note places it before 1853. Likely copied in the 19th century.

history.provenance: Gift of Alexander I. Cotheal (library bookplate inside front cover).
Given by Ch[...] Wexford to William W. Turner in 1853 and then to Alexander I. Cotheal (note in pencil, back flyleaf verso).
Formerly owned by Alexander I. Cotheal (stamp, f. 1r)
